OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1782904686
OL,3,CAndy Burnham promises 'opportunities
OL,4,Cto extend devolution' for Wales
OL,6,FThe former mayor of Greater Manchester
OL,7,Freturned to the city to deliver his
OL,8,Ffirst big speech since returning to
OL,9,FWestminster as an MP and becoming the
OL,10,Ffavourite to replace Keir Starmer as
OL,11,Fprime minister.
OL,13,FIn his speech, Andy Burnham said:
OL,14,F"Westminster has not been working for
OL,15,Fpeople and it has not been working for
OL,16,Fa very long time. In fact, it is
OL,17,Fbroken."
OL,26,@vD@AOUyD@HO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,437,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1782904686
OL,3,CAndy Burnham promises 'opportunities
OL,4,Cto extend devolution' for Wales
OL,6,FHe promised to share out power from
OL,7,FLondon and he pledged to create a
OL,8,F"No10 North" based in Manchester to
OL,9,Fact as "the nerve centre of a rewired
OL,10,FBritain", to redistribute power across
OL,11,Fthe UK's nations and regions.
OL,13,FHe said that operation will transfer
OL,14,Fmore power to Wales, stating: "It will
OL,15,Fbe about offering new opportunities to
OL,16,Fextend devolution in Scotland, Wales
OL,17,Fand Northern Ireland by taking powers
OL,18,Fdeeper down. The people of Dundee and
OL,19,FBangor feel just as distant from
OL,20,FHolyrood and the Senedd, as they do
OL,21,Ffrom Westminster."
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@LO]qD@HOUvD@_OU}D@RO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
