OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1782904686
OL,3,CAndy Burnham promises 'opportunities
OL,4,Cto extend devolution' for Wales
OL,6,FIn his initial response, the First
OL,7,FMinister has expressed scepticism.
OL,8,FRhun ap Iorwerth said: "A Number 10 of
OL,9,Fthe North will mean very little to the
OL,10,Fpeople of Wales.
OL,12,F"I have been arguing for many years
OL,13,Fthat the Westminster system is a
OL,14,Fbroken system. That is why this Welsh
OL,15,FGovernment set out our expectations on
OL,16,Fday one that Wales both needs and
OL,17,Fdeserves a fairer settlement on
OL,18,Ffunding and powers.
OL,26,@pD@XOUtD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,437,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1782904686
OL,3,CAndy Burnham promises 'opportunities
OL,4,Cto extend devolution' for Wales
OL,6,F"Wales already has a new government
OL,7,Fgiving people a new sense of agency,
OL,8,Fpossibility and hope on priorities -
OL,9,Ffrom cutting waiting lists, to rolling
OL,10,Fout fully funded childcare, to
OL,11,Fcreating good jobs.
OL,13,F"Regardless of who leads the UK
OL,14,FGovernment, I will be making the same
OL,15,Fpositive case in a constructive manner
OL,16,F` fair funding and parity of powers
OL,17,Fwith Scotland must be a bare minimum
OL,18,Ffor Wales, and I look forward to
OL,19,Fpursuing a respect agenda that works
OL,20,Fboth ways."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU|D@KO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/13
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
