SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1782904686
OL,3,CAndy Burnham promises 'opportunities
OL,4,Cto extend devolution' for Wales
OL,6,FBut Welsh Labour's interim leader, Ken
OL,7,FSkates welcomed the remarks. He posted
OL,8,Fonline: "Britain is the most
OL,9,Fcentralised and imbalanced country in
OL,10,FEurope. We need devolution within
OL,11,FWales, not just to Wales, ensuring
OL,12,Fpower is closer to communities."
OL,14,FWhile it's yet to become clear what
OL,15,Fsort of powers could be transferred
OL,16,Fand to what level of government,
OL,17,FSenedd or local councils, it's
OL,18,Fbecoming clear Mr Burnham may not
OL,19,Fbring the devolution that Plaid Cymru
OL,20,Fis advocating for.
OL,26,@pD@IOUtD@`O]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/13
